                    "company": "Treant",
                    "description": "As an independent and impartial complaints officer I am responsible for the mediation in the complaint and dispute procedure  for three hospital locations. I inform and guide people, patients and doctors, in the complaint and/or claim process. My main area of interest is to increase patients satisfaction by supporting healthcare professionals, management and the Board of Directors to solve their problems and to restore the therapeutic relationship. \n\nQuality information from individual complaints is also used to develop improvement measures for the benefit of the entire hospital organization. Complaint management provides insights into problem areas by early identification of risk factors and contributes to a (proactive) quality and safety policy. \n\nAs a disclosure coach I am involved in the investigation of critical incidents in the hospital. Concerning critical incidents or internal investigations, I am the connecting link between the patient/relatives and the hospital organization (Board of Directors). My counseling focuses on emotional coaching, ensuring an adequate exchange of information between involved parties, assessing and supporting the needs of patients/relatives and offering them guidance during the whole research process.",
                    "title": "Complaints Officer (klachtenfunctionaris) & Disclosure Coach at Treant Zorggroep",
                    "employment_type": null
                }
            ]
