                    "company": "Martini Ziekenhuis",
                    "description": "October 2015: Member of the Medical Ethics Committee in the Martini Hospital Groningen. Special field of interest Ethical Reflection (Moreel Beraad)\n\nAs a project manager (Care Cluster Oncology) I am responsible for the development of a new quality standard (Martini Standaard voor Oncologie & Welzijn, Martini Borstcentrum). The standard focuses, complementary to medical quality guidelines, on wellbeing aspects for oncology patients. The aim of the standard is to unite high quality requirements of the hospital (Santeon group) with the divers professional guidelines of scientific associations, quality marks of healthcare insurers, and relate to patients perspective (outcome measures) concerning holistic wellbeing criteria. The purpose of the standard is to improve internal organizational processes, but also regulates and contributes to interdisciplinary cooperation with external actors (among others: GPs and primary care). \n\nMy second project relates to the hospital-wide use of quality indicators. Besides the obligatory IGZ and ZiZo-indicators, we focus on the development of RVE indicators (Resultaat Verantwoordelijke Eenheid: i.e. departmental). Within this project, I am responsible for two additional subprojects: 1) Reducing administrative burden on quality indicators and 2) Giving substance and meaning to transparency by means of quality indicators.",
